list.name: Default
list.comment:
Merge branch 'master' of https://github.com/jeffdougherty/dca
- Resized in-game window - Fixed a bug where ships were always recorded as having at least minor fire/flooding - Added a feature where debug mode now goes to random d100 rolls if you don't supply enough rolls, rather than crashing.

task.summary: Default task

Merge branch 'master' of https://github.com/jeffdougherty/dca
Couple housekeeping items as I get ready to start working on this again.

Merge branch 'master' of https://github.com/jeffdougherty/dca
Couple housekeeping items as I get ready to start working on this again.
Added a few more crit types to the big statement.

Merge branch 'master' of https://github.com/jeffdougherty/dca
Stubbed out the rest of the crit types, added some debugging stuff, rewrote how communications hits are tracked to match how the DB actually works.

Merge branch 'master' of https://github.com/jeffdougherty/dca
Finished the flight deck hits, figured out how to represent aircraft being hit.

Merge branch 'master' of https://github.com/jeffdougherty/dca
Starting to hook up the firestarting code, trying to bring some rationality to how fires are going to be tracked.

Merge branch 'master' of https://github.com/jeffdougherty/dca
Apparently I'm not supposed to use str.isnumeric() anymore, str.isdigit() is the new thing in town.

Merge branch 'master' of https://github.com/jeffdougherty/dca
- Added ability to have a reduction mod for fires as well as a severity mod starting out - Added explosion/capsize checks as an event on the 'Game Ship Fire/Flood' table, still need a function to interpret that - Changed parameters so armor_pen value carries into apply_crit() function, to allow for fires when armor hasn't been penetrated. - Finished code to deal with cargo critical hits

Merge branch 'master' of https://github.com/jeffdougherty/dca
- Added function start_flooding() as counterpart to start_fire()

Merge branch 'master' of https://github.com/jeffdougherty/dca
- Retrieving Annex A data for a ship is now spun off as a separate function for easier maintenance.

Merge branch 'master' of https://github.com/jeffdougherty/dca
- Name of SQLite database is now a constant in helperfunctions.py for easier access

Merge branch 'master' of https://github.com/jeffdougherty/dca
- Can now check for severity of fire and flooding and apply immediate consequences - Added a boolean to GSFS table to reflect whether a ship is assigning extra men to DC

Merge branch 'master' of https://github.com/jeffdougherty/dca
- Ship being illuminated by fire now disappears if the fire drops below Major.

Merge branch 'master' of https://github.com/jeffdougherty/dca
- Bugfixes: Now it can apply a hit without crashing. Not correctly, mind...

Merge branch 'master' of https://github.com/jeffdougherty/dca
- Added Verbose Mode for when you want to see the extra output from Debug Mode but don't want to load the dice. - More bugfixes on speed reduction

Merge branch 'master' of https://github.com/jeffdougherty/dca
- Final bugfixes on speed reduction

Merge branch 'master' of https://github.com/jeffdougherty/dca
- Now correctly calculates the number of critical hits.

Merge branch 'master' of https://github.com/jeffdougherty/dca
- Removed pointless global calculation from MainMenu.py

Merge branch 'master' of https://github.com/jeffdougherty/dca
- More bugfixing. Fixed some incorrect SQL syntax. - Explode/capsize checks now go away if the conflagration/flooding is sufficiently reduced - When converting mods to integer values, early exit if it's a 0.

Merge branch 'master' of https://github.com/jeffdougherty/dca
- Updated readme with version and external dependency information.

Merge branch 'master' of https://github.com/jeffdougherty/dca
- Spun rolling for the number of crits off into a separate function, for when we do bomb/torpedo hits. - Added an exiter for crits negated by lack of armor pen, so we don't go through the whole process with them, only to do nothing at the end. (Oy vey)

Merge branch 'master' of https://github.com/jeffdougherty/dca
- Notes on how debug mode works, in anticipation of this actually being seen by someone other than me. - Added a note about how scratchpad is really irrelevant

Merge branch 'master' of https://github.com/jeffdougherty/dca
- One quick readme revision
